      },
      "source": [
        "We see the feature with the largest coefficient value is VORP, indicating this may be the most important variable in predicting a player's points (outside of scoring variables). VORP represents a player's perceived value over potential replacement, indicating the more valuable a player is deemed to be to his team, the higher his points will be, which makes sense as usually the highest scoring players on each team are the players considered some of the most valuable."
      ]
