        "id": "Y2dpI5Ruh_Y_"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Predicting Advanced Stat using basic stats\n",
        "PER is an advanced statistic that aims to summarise a player's impact on the game in a per-minute rating. PER sums up all of a player's positive accomplishments, subtracting negative accomplishments, to return a per-minute value representing a player's positive or negative impact on the game, and their contributions to their team's efforts in winning. PER is a very commonly utilized advanced statistic in today's era of basketball to support and influence opinions on players' impact and allow for comparisons between players, but many fans and even players don't know what goes into determining this rating. By utilizing regression, we can explore how fundamental and basic stats can contribute to a player's overall efficiency, providing insight into the underlying factors that most contribute to a player's performance ratings.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
