      "source": [
        "#create lasso model, using cv = 10 to find optimal lambda.\n",
        "Lasso_CV_per = LassoCV(cv=10, random_state=11, max_iter = 10000)\n",
        "Lasso_CV_per.fit(X_train_per, y_train_per)\n",
        "\n",
        "optimal_lambda = Lasso_CV_per.alpha_\n",
        "print(f\"Optimal Lambda Found: {optimal_lambda:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "#train model with optimal lambda on test data\n",
        "y_pred_per = Lasso_CV_per.predict(X_test_per)\n",
        "\n",
        "#evaluate model\n",
        "mse = mean_squared_error(y_test_per, y_pred_per)\n",
        "R2 = r2_score(y_test_per, y_pred_per)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Mean Squared Error (MSE): {mse:.2f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"R-squared (R2): {R2:.2f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "#get variable names and coeff values\n",
        "lasso_coef_per = pd.DataFrame({\"variable\": X_basic_stats.columns, \"Coefficient\": Lasso_CV_per.coef_})\n",
        "\n",
        "# Filter out features with zero coefficients (those removed by Lasso)\n",
        "important_features = lasso_coef_per[lasso_coef_per['Coefficient'] != 0].sort_values(by='Coefficient', ascending=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Important Features (Non-Zero Coefficients from Lasso):\")\n",
        "display(important_features)\n",
        "print(\"Number of features\", len(important_features))\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "r9-BCtUKnSdh"
      },
      "source": [
        "We see again that the lasso model has worked in variable selection by reducing the coefficient value for 9 variables to 0, and we similarly see a slight decrease in model metrics as our lasso model explains 70% of the variation in PER with MSE = 11.43, indicating slightly worse performance for improved interpretability."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 47,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
