        "Overall, we can see the scoring percentage metrics, such as FG%, eFG%, FT%, seem to be the most important positive factors contributing to PER, indicating that the most positive value a player can contribute on the court is to score the ball efficiently, regardless of volume. We also observe that TOV and MP interaction terms with eFG% are the biggest negative coefficient values, suggesting that high turnovers are still the largest contributing factor to negative impact on team winning, and minutes played without contributing can significantly detract from a player's PER. Other notable negative coefficients include FGA, 3PA, 2PA, Age, GS, and DRB, implying that inefficiency in shot selection or simply playing more games and minutes without contributing positively can lower a player's perceived impact."
