        "In this section, we have built and analyzed several regression models for predicting key metrics such as player points (PTS) and player efficiency rating (PER) using various fundamental basketball statistics. For PTS, refined linear models were created using non direct socring statsistics, showing a strong linear model with R2 = 0.97, and MSE = 1.17. However, due to the large number of predictors, we wanted to increase the interpretability of our model. We then moved on to lasso regression with CV to perform feature selection, which revealed VORP as the most significant indicator of PTS among all non-scoring variables."
